reviewText: All details previously posted are true.......but the print qualities/transfers are much better than average for such a PD collection. The British titles look especially good. I'd swear that the transfer of THE GHOUL was lifted from MGM's region 1 DVD!  It's that good. Some title cards have been slightly altered such as the addition of DR. MANIAC: above the original title for THE MAN WHO CHANGED HIS MIND.  It's great to have 18 titles on a single disc. My only gripe is the absence of a "play all" feature and lack of chapter stop listing. You also can't seem to go back to the main menu (at least on my player) during a film--it has to play all the way through or you have to skip all the way to the end of the film.  I hope Firecake Entertainment (a British distribution company) keeps these sets coming. I see that they have an old dark house mysteries collection up for preorder.
